cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on leveraging SmartNICs for interactive workloads and stream processing. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses serverless compute and resource allocation in cloud computing. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is relevant as the paper presents a framework for running interactive workloads on SmartNICs. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of ASIC-based NICs with a dense grid of NPU cores. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper presents an event-based programming abstraction for composing and executing lambdas on SmartNICs.
